The '''International Institute of Physics''' (IIP) is a research unit of [[UFRN]],<ref name="tribunadonorte">{{cite web|url=http://tribunadonorte.com.br/noticia/ufrn-inaugura-sede-do-instituto-internacional-de-fisica/149206|title=UFRN inaugura sede do Instituto Internacional de Física - Tribuna do Norte|publisher=tribunadonorte.com.br|accessdate=2015-12-16}}</ref> located in [[Natal, Rio Grande do Norte]], [[Brazil]] with a strong international outlook permanently focused on frontier areas of [[theoretical physics]].  In addition to its [[research]] activities,<ref>http://iip.ufrn.br/publications</ref> the IIP promotes regular workshops, schools, conferences, as well as public lectures.<ref>http://iip.ufrn.br/events</ref> Candidates to IIP openings are selected by international experts, under an open competition regime.

