'''Lee Ann Jung''' is an American [[Teacher|educator]], [[Professors in the United States|professor]], author, and international [[consultant]]. Jung began her career as a [[Special education|special educator]] in 1994.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ascd.org/Publications/ascd-authors/lee-ann-jung.aspx|title=ASCD Author - Lee Ann Jung|last=ASCD|website=www.ascd.org|access-date=2018-06-04}}</ref> Much of Jung's work centers on supporting international schools{{clarify|date=June 2018}} to include and support students with disabilities and [[Learning disability|learning differences]].<ref name="authorcentral">{{Cite web|url=https://authorcentral.amazon.com/gp/profile|title=Amazon Sign In|website=authorcentral.amazon.com|access-date=2018-06-04}}</ref>{{failed verification|date=June 2018}} Jung developed and leads an international inclusive leadership program,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.studentgrowth.org/internationalinclusion/|title=International Inclusive Education Program - ASCD Student Growth Center|website=www.studentgrowth.org|access-date=2018-06-04}}</ref> the world's largest program devoted to preparing teachers in international schools in the area of special education and inclusion.<ref name="authorcentral" />{{failed verification|date=June 2018}} She was 2017-2018 chair of the Classroom Assessment Special Interest Group of the American Educational Research Association.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aera.net/|title=American Educational Research Association > Home|website=www.aera.net|access-date=2018-06-04}}</ref>

Jung is considered{{by whom|date=June 2018}} an international authority in the areas of [[Educational assessment|assessment]] and [[Grading in education|grading]] for students with disabilities and inclusion in international schools.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}} Her notable works in these areas include the bestselling{{clarify|date=June 2018}} book, ''Grading Exceptional and Struggling Learners'',<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://us.corwin.com/en-us/nam/grading-exceptional-and-struggling-learners/book234823|title=Grading Exceptional and Struggling Learners|date=2018-05-14|work=Corwin|access-date=2018-06-04}}</ref> and a new book, ''From Goals to Growth: Intervention and Support in Every Classroom''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ascd.org/Publications/Books/Overview/From-Goals-to-Growth.aspx|title=From Goals to Growth: Intervention & Support in Every Classroom|last=ASCD|website=www.ascd.org|access-date=2018-06-04}}</ref> In addition to her five books,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Lee-Ann-Jung/e/B005K2SGIG|title=Amazon.com: Lee Ann Jung: Books, Biography, Blog, Audiobooks, Kindle|website=www.amazon.com|access-date=2018-06-04}}</ref> Jung's more than 40 articles have appeared in journals such as ''[[Phi Delta Kappa]]n'' and [http://www.ascd.org/publications/educational-leadership.aspx ''Educational Leadership'']<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.leadinclusion.org/pubs|title=Lead Inclusion|website=LEE ANN JUNG, PHD {{!}} LEAD INCLUSION {{!}} Lexington, KY|access-date=2018-06-04}}</ref> as well as many other peer-reviewed publications.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&as_sdt=0,18&q=Lee+ANn+jung&btnG=|title=Google Scholar|website=scholar.google.com|access-date=2018-06-04}}</ref>

